Who are we?

The CBCS Coding Club comprises a group of students and early career researchers in CBCS and SENV at the University of Queensland. Coding Club is currently co-led by:

Kristine (Tin) Buenafe

Tin is a PhD candidate from the Philippines working on climate-smart marine conservation planning with a particular focus in the high seas. While she enjoys coding all-day, working to develop reproducible tools and frameworks used to facilitate the uptake of climate-smart approaches in on-the-ground, applied conservation planning approaches, she wishes to continue navigating the science-policy interface, particularly in relation to the Biodiversity Beyond National Jurisdiction (BBNJ) Agreement.
